Package: easyRaschBayes
Title: Bayesian Rasch Analysis Using 'brms'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Magnus", "Johansson",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "pgmj@pm.me",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1669-592X")),
    person("Giacomo", "Bignardi",
           role = "ctb",
           comment = "RMU reliability code"))
Description: Provides functions to reproduce classic Rasch analysis features
    using Bayesian item response theory (IRT) models fitted with 'brms'.
    Supports both dichotomous Rasch models and polytomous partial credit or
    rating scale models. Features include posterior predictive item fit,
    person fit, differential item functioning (DIF), local dependence
    assessment via Q3 residual correlations, dimensionality assessment via
    residual principal components analysis, person-item targeting plots,
    item category probability curves, and reliability via Relative
    Measurement Uncertainty.
